    "Although the uniform refinement is straightforward, it serves here to explain the terminology.",
    "Depending on the number of spatial dimensions, D ∈ {2, 3}, each cell marked for refinement is split into four or eight child-cells for 2D and 3D cases, respectively.",
    "The cell that has been split1.",
    "Computation of the metric field is referred to as the root or parent cell.",
    "All cells without child cells are called leaf cells and represent the current grid."
